p: Results: Based on the results presented, the VMN delivered the highest emitted dose (70.49 ± 1.86 %, distal at 5 LPM), (67.84 ± 0.98 %, distal at 11 LPM) and (101.03 ± 5.45 %, proximal at 5 LPM), (107.40 ± 5.51 %, proximal at 11 LPM) at both attachment setups and supplemental gas flow rates compared with the JN (48.43 ± 6.92 %, distal at 5 LPM) & (47.94 ± 3.48 %, distal at 11 LPM) and (56.86 ± 1.12 %, proximal at 5 LPM), (53.48 ± 5.22 %, proximal at 11 LPM).
